criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

        Adult kidney transplants, with high immunological risk, who consented to participate in the
        study by signing the informed consent form. The high immune risk is defined by:

          -  Positive pre-transplant T-lymphocyte cross-test by flow cytometry (channel deviation
             greater than 62);

          -  Flow cytometry pre-transplantation positive B lymphocyte cross-test (channel deviation
             greater than 112);

          -  Calculated panel reactivity greater than 50% in class I and / or class II;

          -  Presence in the pre-transplantation serum of donor class I and / or II anti-Human
             Leukocyte Antigen antibodies with intensity and fluorescence greater than 1000;

          -  Occurrence of cellular or antibody-mediated rejection within 30 days prior to the date
             of the protocol biopsy.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with contraindication to renal graft biopsy;

          -  Patients whose biopsy fragments are not representative;

          -  Patients with graft dysfunction in whom renal graft biopsy is indicated within 4 weeks
             prior to protocol biopsy.
